Package: decomposer
Title: Generic Decomposition Framework for Discrete-Time Simulations
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Austin", "Carter", , "aucarter@uw.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: A model-agnostic decomposition framework that attributes changes in
    simulation outcomes to individual input factors using Das Gupta or Shapley
    decomposition. Any calibrated discrete-time simulation model can use the
    decomposer by implementing a small set of S3 methods: run the model,
    summarize outputs, and construct counterfactual inputs. Supports two
    counterfactual types: "change_since" (hold factor at baseline-year value)
    and "total_impact" (set factor to zero).
